*.qcow2

# Private keys consumed at runtime as ssh -i argument (OpenSSH refuses
# keys with mode looser than 0600, and git can't store 0600). Their
# public counterparts (.pub) stay tracked so the flake evaluates on
# a fresh clone.
#
# The fleet-CA / per-host / org-root / bootstrap-token files are NOT
# gitignored: they're consumed via `builtins.readFile` + `environment.etc`
# (mode-insensitive), and tracking them keeps `nix flake check` working
# from a clean clone without the operator having to run the regenerator
# script first. They're demo identities — see secrets/README.md.
secrets/demo-ssh-key
